{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-85394a2a72930dbc","input":{"filename":"incident_action_report.md","title":"Prioritized Action Report – Incident Commander","markdown":"# Prioritized Action Report – Incident Commander (under 500 words)\n\n**Evidence**\n- Dossier loaded for Agent 06‑incident‑commander (SRE incident triage role). \n- Record analysis (limit = 10) returned three high‑impact items with risk/opportunity scores.\n\n## 1. Immediate Containment – **Record 06‑A**\n- **Title:** Incident commander priority case\n- **Owner:** SRE (self)\n- **Status:** urgent\n- **Impact:** 43,902 (highest)\n- **Risk score:** 7 (high)\n- **Opportunity score:** 6.4\n- **Summary:** Core responsibility – build incident timeline & next‑action checklist from alerts/logs.\n\n**Action**\n1. Confirm current alert feed availability (e.g., Prometheus, PagerDuty).  \n2. Pull the latest logs for the affected service (last 2 h) and generate a timeline skeleton.  \n3. Tag the incident with an **owner** (SRE lead) and publish an initial update to the incident channel within **15 min**.\n\n## 2. Unblock Critical Dependency – **Record 06‑C**\n- **Title:** Incident commander blocked follow‑up\n- **Owner:** SRE\n- **Status:** blocked\n- **Impact:** 19,266\n- **Risk score:** 7 (high)\n- **Opportunity score:** 1.9\n- **Summary:** Requires cross‑functional coordination before safe recommendation.\n\n**Action**\n1. Identify the blocking team (e.g., Platform, Security) via the incident tracker.  \n2. Schedule a rapid sync (≤30 min) to resolve dependencies (access, data, or tooling).  \n3. Document the unblock steps in the incident timeline; update the risk rating once cleared.\n\n## 3. Review Routine Item – **Record 06‑B**\n- **Title:** Incident commander routine queue item\n- **Owner:** SRE\n- **Status:** in_review\n- **Impact:** 9,678\n- **Risk score:** 1 (low)\n- **Opportunity score:** 1\n- **Summary:** Lower‑risk operational task, useful for baseline comparison.\n\n**Action**\n1. Perform a quick sanity check (e.g., verify that existing runbooks are up‑to‑date).  \n2. If no immediate issues, mark as **completed** after documentation.\n\n## Assumptions & Uncertainties\n- The incident is currently active and alerts are flowing; if not, containment steps will be adjusted.\n- Cross‑functional blockers can be reached within the next 30 min; longer delays will elevate the risk.\n- No additional high‑risk records exist beyond the top 3 returned by the analysis tool.\n\n## Next Update Timeline\n- **T+15 min:** Publish initial timeline (Record 06‑A).\n- **T+30 min:** Resolve blockers (Record 06‑C) or raise escalation if unresolved.\n- **T+45 min:** Complete routine review (Record 06‑B) and finalize the first‑hour incident report.\n\n---\n*Report generated by Agent 06‑incident‑commander. All actions prioritize containment, customer impact, clear ownership, and timely communication.*"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:06:10.483Z"}}
